<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="1294" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[178,1085,1256,1395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">
C o m m e n t: The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2009" box="[641,748,1256,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sengleti">
<emphasis box="[641,748,1256,1278]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">L. sengleti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a single male (
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294" pagination="211 - 219" refId="ref11133" refString="PACE R. (1984): Nuove Aleocharinae microftalme mediterranee e dell'Iran, del Museum d'Histoire naturelle di Ginevra (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Archives Scientifiques Geneve 37: 211 - 219." type="journal article" year="1984">PACE 1984</bibRefCitation>
). The aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[412,489,1285,1307]" captionStart="Figs 49-54" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1491,1511]" captionTargetBox="[186,1079,879,1436]" captionTargetId="figure-319@16.[178,1084,873,1476]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 49-54: Leptusa ionopolitana PACE (49-51), L. amisensis PACE (52), and L. sengleti PACE (53- 54): (49, 53) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50-52) spermatheca; (54) male sternite VII. Scale bars: 54: 0.2 mm; 49-53: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276633/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) and the male sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[790,868,1285,1307]" captionStart="Figs 49-54" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1491,1511]" captionTargetBox="[186,1079,879,1436]" captionTargetId="figure-319@16.[178,1084,873,1476]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 49-54: Leptusa ionopolitana PACE (49-51), L. amisensis PACE (52), and L. sengleti PACE (53- 54): (49, 53) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50-52) spermatheca; (54) male sternite VII. Scale bars: 54: 0.2 mm; 49-53: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276633/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
) are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2009" box="[268,399,1315,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piciformis">
<emphasis box="[268,399,1315,1336]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">L. piciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2009" box="[450,575,1315,1336]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flagrifera">
<emphasis box="[450,575,1315,1336]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">L. flagrifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively. This species was the first representative of the genus to become known from 
<collectingCountry box="[618,662,1344,1365]" name="Iran" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">Iran</collectingCountry>
. It is currently known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1041,1085,1344,1365]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation box="[267,336,1373,1395]" captionStart="Map 4" captionStartId="14.[178,223,731,751]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,707]" captionTargetId="figure-1@14.[178,1084,212,707]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Map 4: Distributions of the Leptusa species of the subgenus Roubaliusa SCHEERPELTZ in northern Iran: L. sengleti PACE (filled square), L. piciformis nov.sp. (open circle), L. flagrifera nov.sp. (open circle), L. delphiniformis nov.sp. (filled circle), and L. soriciformis nov.sp. (open square). Localities where only females were found are omitted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276631/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1294">Map 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
